@NODE Vorwort
Hello World!

A lot of fun with the program Aminet-Readme-Creator.

1. The program supports generating a .readme file, 
   that additionally confirms to the new structure.

2. Additionally the program converts "any" .readme file
   to a standard design. 
   Since verson 1.3 it takes the lines below the header
   too.

A .readme file is necessary when you upload a file to
Aminet.

The program takes control about the conventions of the
structure, the length of entries and the length of the
name of the file.


There are several programs to create a .readme file in
the Aminet, but all of them are old and does not cover
the new structure of the Aminet-readme-file.
A new and major entry is the group "Architecture", and
this is not supported by the old programs.

The programs I examined where:
uprc, arf-wizard, AmiReadMeGen, ARC, CAR, LazyReadme,
Readmemaker, ReportPlus (Version 4.71), CEDMakeReadme,
Com2Readme, MakeRMThor.
ReportPlus with Version 6 and higher supports the
"Architecutre" field, but does only run with OS 3.9.
            _
         _ //
         \X/
Thanks, Amiga...
@ENDNODE

@NODE Require
With AmigaOS 2.1 and  AmigaOS 3.x no problem occured.

To run the program you need:
- dos.library      (in ROM)
- graphics.library (in ROM)
- diskfont.library

                                   - - -

