@NODE Usage
Documentation

- Copy the whole folder where ever you want by Drag and Drop.
  All needed files will be copied that way.

- Start the program by Doubleclick the programm-icon.
  After the launch you see a window on your screen.

- The pulldowns are:

  -------------------------------------------------------------------------
  Project

  Open any readme  ..................  Reads "any" .readme file, that you
                                       specify will full path, name and 
                                       suffix.
                                       Example: RAM:Test.readme
                                       It is not needed that the fields
                                       has to be in the same order as it
                                       uses the program. While reading
                                       a readme file the program connects
                                       the content to the right place.
                                       Therefore the program helps you to
                                       convert a readme file to a standard
                                       design.

  Save as Default  ..................  Saves the inputs as default.
                                       This selection becomes activ only
                                       when all recommanded fields has been
                                       filled.
                                       Is there a file "Default.readme"
                                       it will be read and the content will
                                       be shown. Only the recommanded fields
                                       has to be changed / filled.

  Save as .readme  ..................  Saves the input as file.
                                       This selection becomes activ only
                                       when all recommanded fields has been
                                       filled.
                                       The path is RAM: plus the name of
                                       the readme-file. This file has
                                       nothing to do with the default-file,
                                       that means it will not be load while
                                       starting the program as default. Do
                                       you want to save the content for
                                       later on, you should choose selection
                                       "Save as Default" (see discription
                                       there).

  About...  .........................  Short information about the programm.

  Quit  .............................  Close the programm.

  -------------------------------------------------------------------------

  Recommended

  Short  ............................  This field needs to be the first line
                                       of the readme file. It lets you 
                                       specify a short description of your 
                                       upload which will be displayed in 
                                       Aminet's directory tree and in the 
                                       daily e-mail newsletters. 
                                       This description should not be longer
                                       than 40 characters. Don't repeat the 
                                       file name here and do not include any
                                       version numbers or target platforms
                                       in the Short: field 
                                       - try to explain what the program
                                       *does*. Music should specify the style
                                       and author. Don't boast or use much 
                                       uppercase. 
                                       If your upload requires a language 
                                       other than English, please mention 
                                       that language in the Short: 
                                       description. 
                                       e.g. Aminet-Readme-Creator (german).

  Author/Uploader  ..................  This is the place where you can 
                                       indicate who created the piece of 
                                       software you are uploading. 
                                       The Author will be automaticially
                                       set by the program as Uploader.
                                       Should it be differnt, you have to
                                       change the .readme file manually.

  Type  .............................  Here you can specify a target 
                                       top-directory for your upload. 
                                       Check the index of Aminet 
                                       directories for a list of possible
                                       values. 
                                       Afterwards you have to select the
                                       sub-directory with the pulldown
                                       "Subtype" (see discription there).

        biz  - Business software
        comm - Communications
        demo - Gfx and sound demos
        dev  - Development software
        disk - Disk/Harddisk tools
        driver Hardware driver
        docs - Text documents
        game - Games
        gfx  - Graphics
        misc - Miscellaneous
        mods - Music modules
        mus  - Musical software
        pix  - Pictures
        text - Text related
        util - Utilities

  Subtype  ..........................  Definition, which sub-directory
                                       should be used to upload your file.
                                       The directory should match the
                                       character of the file / content.
                                       This pulldown changes itself in
                                       combination of the selection made
                                       by the selection "Type"
                                       (see discription there.)

  Architecture
    m68k-amigaos  ...................  Binaries for AmigaOS 1+2+3
    ppc-amigaos  ....................  Binaries for AmigaOS 4
    ppc-morphos  ....................  Binaries for MorphOS
    ppc-powerup  ....................  Binaries for PowerUp
    ppc-warpup  .....................  Binaries for WarpUp
    i386-aros  ......................  Binaries for AROS
    i386-amithlon  ..................  Binaries for Amithlon
    generic  ........................  If your package does not contain 
                                       *any* binaries, use "generic".

  Distribution  .....................  There are two legal values for 
                                       this field, "NoCD" and "Aminet"
                                       - do not specify anything else
                                       here. 
          
    Aminet  .........................  With "Distribution: Aminet" you
                                       restrict distribution of your 
                                       upload to Aminet (including 
                                       Aminet CDs and other media),
                                       i.e. you stop other groups 
                                       from redistributing it. 
    NoCD  ...........................  With "Distributrion: NoCD", you make
                                       sure that your upload will not be
                                       distributed on the CDs or DVDs
                                       created by the Aminet team.


  -------------------------------------------------------------------------

  Options

  Version  ..........................  The version number of your upload.
                                       Don't use version numbers in file
                                       name if possible. 

  Replaces  .........................  Here you can specify files that 
                                       should be replaced by your upload. 
                                       Give full path, Unix wildcards are 
                                       allowed in the filename. Examples: 

                                       Replaces: biz/patch/Test1.lha.
                                       Replaces: biz/patch/Test* 

                                       You can specify several files here,
                                       separated by semicolons. You do not
                                       need to specify this field if you 
                                       are going to overwrite an existing
                                       package which has the same name as
                                       your current upload. 

  Requires  .........................  Other Aminet archives that your 
                                       upload needs to work, with full path.
                                       Example: 

                                       Requires: util/libs/mui38usr.lha 

                                       Also name memory and chipset 
                                       requirements here. 

  Kurz  .............................  40 characters are allowed here.
                                       This is the German version of Short:
                                       (see above). 


- The program can be terminated while pressing CTRL-C, with th Close Gadget
  in the top-left corner or with the pulldown-selction "Quit ...".

@ENDNODE


@NODE Version
0.1  11.08.2006 - First version (2 hours in total development)
0.2  12.08.2006 - SAVE AS Routine
                - Window with hints for long entries
                - Save Default and read default
0.3  13.08.2006 - Changed menuestructur in a lean structur
                  (combinded the pulldowns in only 3 Menus)
0.31 14.08.2006 - Some bugs removed
0.4  15.08.2006 - Completed the menustructur
                - Moved "Version" to the "Options" pulldown
0.5  19.08.2006 - Input routine for "all" external .readme Files
                  (Very variable caused by line-by-line analyse of the content
                - When the recommanded fields are filled by the Input-Routine
                  the SAVE-Pulldown is going to be activ already.
                - Some Bug-Fixes removed
0.6  20.08.2006 - Some Bug-Fixes removed
                - Filetest routine with dos.library
0.7  03.11.2006 - Completed the menustructur
1.0  20.02.2007 - Menu completed. The entries of MODS are now implemented.
                  There are more than 63 differnt MOD-directories, but the pulldown
                  menu can only handle 62 entries, therefore the structure has to
                  be reduced to selected entries.
1.1  01.03.2007 - Bug fixed: The word "Version" was not found while import /convert
                  a readme-file, because the check of 3 characters was to less.
                  The import routine could not identify the keyword "Version". 
                  With a check of 4 characters, means "Vers", the word can be 
                  identified and the content will be used.
1.2  02.03.2007 - Bug fixed: Caused by the new MOD-Type the Subtype für MISC was
                  not displayed anymore. This is correct now.
1.3  05.03.2007 - Uploader will not be set equal to the Author, when a readm-file
                  will be converted.
                - All textlines below the header, written in a file, will be used
                  in the converted file.
                - The check, whether a readme-file is ready to save or not, happens
                  now on base of the recommended keywords, they have to be filled out.
                  In the past it could happen, that a readme-file could be saved,
                  although not all recommended fields where complete, but in the
                  memory the fields from a file before had the complete information.
1.4  18.03.2007 - Bug fixed: The optionally lines (Replaces...Kurz) would not saved
                  while converting a .readme, because the routine expected, that 
                  they have been selected by pulldown first.
1.41 29.04.2007 - Pulldowns actualized:
                  Added:  dev/lib + game/edit + game/strat + misc/os
                  Deleted:misc/kids + pix/wfm
1.42 29.10.2007 - Pulldowns aktualized:
                  Added: docs/hard + driver/... + gfx/x11 + pix/3dobj + pix/picon
                  Deleted: gfx/3dobj + gfx/board + hard/... + misc/x11

@ENDNODE

